# Vision Replay — Video Frame Analysis

When working with video files, use the HelixLab vision-replay scripts for frame extraction and analysis.

## Quick Start

1. Get metadata: `bash skills/vision-replay/scripts/video-info.sh "<video>"`
2. Normalize: `bash skills/vision-replay/scripts/normalize-video.sh "<video>" "/tmp/frames/normalized.mp4"`
3. Deduplicate: `bash skills/vision-replay/scripts/dedupe-video.sh "/tmp/frames/normalized.mp4" "/tmp/frames/deduped.mp4" <threshold>`
4. Contact sheet: `bash skills/vision-replay/scripts/contact-sheet.sh "/tmp/frames/deduped.mp4" "/tmp/frames/sheet.png"`
5. Extract frames: `bash skills/vision-replay/scripts/extract-frames.sh "/tmp/frames/deduped.mp4" "/tmp/frames" 10`
6. Batch if >20 frames: `bash skills/vision-replay/scripts/batch-frames.sh "/tmp/frames" 15`
7. Clean up: `bash skills/vision-replay/scripts/cleanup.sh "/tmp/frames"`

## Workflow Guides

- Animation: `skills/vision-replay/workflows/animation-analysis.md`
- Page load: `skills/vision-replay/workflows/page-load-analysis.md`
- Workflow review: `skills/vision-replay/workflows/workflow-review.md`

## FPS Selection

| Use Case | FPS |
|----------|-----|
| Fast animations (<200ms) | 30-60 |
| Standard transitions (200-500ms) | 10-15 |
| Slow transitions (>500ms) | 5-10 |
| Page load | Progressive (use extract-progressive.sh) |
| Workflow review | 2-3 or scene-detect |

## Dedup Thresholds

| Analysis Type | Threshold | Preserves |
|---------------|-----------|-----------|
| Animation | 1 | Subtle easing, fades, micro-interactions |
| Page load | 3 | Progressive rendering changes |
| Workflow review | 15 | Major state changes only |

## Record Browser

HelixLab also includes a browser recording skill. Launch a headed Chrome with recording toolbar and annotation tools:

```bash
bash skills/record-browser/scripts/install-browser.sh  # one-time setup
bash skills/record-browser/scripts/launch-recorder.sh "[url]"
```

Recordings save as WebM. Parse `HELIX_SAVED=<path>` from stdout to get the file path, then analyze with the vision-replay pipeline above. See `AGENTS.md` for the full Record Browser workflow.
